From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Petr=20=C5=A0tetiar?= <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
Date: Thu, 27 Jun 2024 14:27:28 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] scripts: boot_measure.sh: provide measurements via debuginfo
 command
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Currently the Lua script `boot_measurements.lua` collects quite handy boot
time metrics, but unfortunatelly those metrics are not available via
getDebugInformation script, thus missing in most bug reports. So lets
fix it by hooking in the standard init script `debuginfo` command which
would dump the `/tmp/amx_mon_objects.log` into the output.

References: PCF-1168, PCF-1242, PCF-1257
Signed-off-by: Petr Å tetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Petr Štetiar <petr.stetiar@prplfoundation.org>
---
 scripts/boot_measure.sh | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/scripts/boot_measure.sh b/scripts/boot_measure.sh
index 14519484549b..0e95b7d478df 100644
--- a/scripts/boot_measure.sh
+++ b/scripts/boot_measure.sh
@@ -10,7 +10,10 @@ case $1 in
         $0 stop
         $0 start
         ;;
+    debuginfo)
+        cat /tmp/amx_mon_objects.log
+        ;;
     *)
-        echo "Usage : $0 [start|boot|stop]"
+        echo "Usage : $0 [start|boot|stop|debuginfo]"
         ;;
 esac
